Vice President Biden issued a statement condemning the attack on United Nations peacekeepers in Mali, which resulted in the death of nine peacekeepers from Niger. He extended his condolences to the families, friends, and government of Niger. The attack is part of a series of similar incidents that have occurred in the past 15 months, resulting in the deaths of 30 peacekeepers and injuries to 90 others. The Vice President emphasized the bravery and importance of peacekeepers in restoring peace and bringing security to civilians around the world. He also expressed the United States' strong support for U.N. peacekeepers and their contributions to international peace and security.